com.versant.fund
Interface AttrTraversable

All Superinterfaces:
Attr, java.lang.Cloneable
All Known Subinterfaces:
AttrHandle, AttrHandleArray
public interface AttrTraversable
extends Attr

Used to specify path attribute to construct predicate for path queries.

Suppose you have the following object model: 

   __________       ________       _______
  | EMPLOYEE |     | GARAGE |     |  CAR  |
  |          |     |        |     |       |
  | garages-------->cars--------->color |
  |__________|     |________|     |_______|

To find all Employees who own a Red colored Car, you can formulate a predicate for a path query as follows: 

 AttrHandleArray garages = session.newAttrHandleArray("garages");
 AttrHandleArray cars    = session.newAttrHandleArray("cars");
 AttrString      color   = session.newAttrString("color");
 AttrString garageToCarToColor =
     garages.pathToHandleArray(cars).pathToString(color);
 Predicate pred = garageToCarToColor.eq("Red");

See Also:
AttrHandle, AttrHandleArray
